      "passage_text": "In a transgenic mouse model of Alzheimer's disease (5xFAD, n = 60 mice), pharmacological depletion of microglia via CSF1R inhibitor PLX5622 reduced amyloid plaque burden by 35 % at 6 months but did not improve spatial memory in the Barnes maze. This suggests microglial removal has plaque-clearing but not cognitive benefits."
