      "passage_text": "Sharp-wave ripples (SWRs) recorded from hippocampal CA1 in sleeping rats (n = 30) co-occurred with cortical slow oscillations and spindles in 78 % of events, consistent with the active systems consolidation hypothesis. Optogenetic disruption of SWRs during slow-wave sleep impaired novel object recognition 24 h later (p < 0.001)."
    },
